        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 2:15PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 215 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Riviera Beach, or 8 miles east of Sarita, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Kenedy County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
